    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-02T13:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-02T13:36:00-05:00" n="949"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d949">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3008.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-02T12:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 2, 1912—12 noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Refugees arriving at Acapulco report intolerable conditions in Chiapas. Many
                    American planters in Tabasco without protection are preparing to leave. Our
                    military attaché believes conditions not improved in Morelos or Guerrero. The
                    situation grows steadily worse in Tlaxcala and Puebla and there is now organized
                    rebellion in Vera Cruz, where great devastation is being committed. For the
                    first time I have to report disorders and armed movements in Tamaulipas.
                    Practically all of the States of Chihuahua and Durango, with a part of Coahuila
                    and a large portion of Zacatecas, have apparently passed out of the control of
                    the Federal Government. In Sinaloa and Michoacán there are armed movements and
                    in Hidalgo trouble in anticipated. The American emigration from all parts of the
                    Republic, and especially from this city, continues to be very heavy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
